From 36c3cdc874be0fe468e0831af034a3918c9bee51 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yunjian Wang <wangyunjian@huawei.com>
Date: Mon, 12 Apr 2021 22:41:18 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] i40e: Fix use-after-free in i40e_client_subtask()
Patch-mainline: v5.13-rc5
Git-commit: 38318f23a7ef86a8b1862e5e8078c4de121960c3
References: CVE-2021-46991 bsc#1220575 

[ Upstream commit 38318f23a7ef86a8b1862e5e8078c4de121960c3 ]

Currently the call to i40e_client_del_instance frees the object
pf->cinst, however pf->cinst->lan_info is being accessed after
the free. Fix this by adding the missing return.

Addresses-Coverity: ("Read from pointer after free")
Fixes: 7b0b1a6d0ac9 ("i40e: Disable iWARP VSI PETCP_ENA flag on netdev down events")
Signed-off-by: Yunjian Wang <wangyunjian@huawei.com>
Signed-off-by: Tony Nguyen <anthony.l.nguyen@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Denis Kirjanov <denis.kirjanov@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_client.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_client.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_client.c
index dd65a54cc52f..0359591a21d0 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_client.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_client.c
@@ -400,6 +400,7 @@ void i40e_client_subtask(struct i40e_pf *pf)
 				clear_bit(__I40E_CLIENT_INSTANCE_OPENED,
 					  &cdev->state);
 				i40e_client_del_instance(pf);
+				return;
 			}
 		}
 	}
